        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23333",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The default encoding is defined by current locale.\n\nDo you see it's useful to have an option to set it to something different?\n\nYeah.\nThat may be good to have something like setDefaultEncoding($encodeng) where null means 'encoding defined by current locale' and any other value is converted to string and used as encoding.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-06T05:15:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-06T05:15:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23342",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=techi",
                        "name": "techi",
                        "displayName": "Michal Vrchota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I disagree.\n\nEncoding and locale are 2 separated things. Locale i.e. is czech, russian or german. But encoding is i.e. UTF-8. If you look at declaration of drawString() - you will see it calls Zend_Pdf_Resource_Font::encodeString() which is wrapper for iconv()\nThat means encoding is the first param for iconv() function. So there is no way to convert locale to encoding\n\nAnyway alternatively you can use native iconv_set_encoding() to set default encoding. Unluckily there is no reference in documentation about such behaviour. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=techi",
                        "name": "techi",
                        "displayName": "Michal Vrchota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-06T06:53:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-06T06:53:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23352",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Current locale may contain encoding information, ex:\n{code}\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, 'cs_CZ.ISO-8859-2');\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, 'cs_CZ.UTF-8');\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, 'de_DE.ISO-8859-1);\n{code}\n\niconv() uses it if empty string is provided as 'to' or 'from' encoding.\n\nOn the other hand I definitely agree, it should be described in the documentation more clear, probably in addition to the adding setDefaultEncoding() method.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-06T11:27:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-06T11:27:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23353",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=techi",
                        "name": "techi",
                        "displayName": "Michal Vrchota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "OK i see. I thought u mean Zend_Locale. I agree the documentation should be more clear. That is the main reason for creating this issue",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=techi",
                        "name": "techi",
                        "displayName": "Michal Vrchota",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-06T11:33:43.000+0000",
